Japan FSA Minister Jimi Declines to Comment on Olympus’s Scandal

-- B y   S h i n g o   K a w a m o t o
-- 
2011-10-21T02:33:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/japan-fsa-minister-jimi-declines-to-comment-on-olympus-s-scandal.html
Japan ’s Financial Services Minister
Shozaburo Jimi declined to comment on  Olympus Corp. (7733) ’s scandal
over payments to acquisition advisers, adding that in general,
if there are any rule breaches, necessary examinations will be
carried out accordingly. He was speaking to reporters in  Tokyo 
today.   To contact the reporter on this story:
